SUMMARY: WHAT YOU NEED TO DO
======================================================================

ACTION ITEMS FOR THE USER:

1. ACTION RECOGNITION TRAINING (REQUIRED for meaningful predictions)
   The LSTM classifier has random weights. You need a labeled dataset.
   Options:
     a) NTU RGB+D 120 — largest skeleton action dataset
     b) UCF-Crime — real CCTV footage (requires keypoint extraction)
     c) Your own labeled CCTV clips
   When ready, run the training scripts in training/.

2. REAL CAMERA STREAMS (REQUIRED for production)
   Add RTSP URLs to config/default.yaml under cameras.sources
   Test with: python scripts/demo_ingestion.py

3. MODEL WEIGHTS (REQUIRED for detection/pose)
   Download or place the following in models/:
     - yolov8m.pt (detection)
     - yolov8m-pose.pt (pose estimation)
     - action_classifier_v1.pt (trained classifier)

4. NOTIFICATION CHANNELS (OPTIONAL)
   - Webhook: add endpoints to config/default.yaml
   - Email: add SMTP credentials to config/default.yaml

5. PRODUCTION DATABASE (OPTIONAL — SQLite works for dev)
   - Start PostgreSQL: docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d
   - Run migrations: alembic upgrade head

6. GPU DEPLOYMENT (OPTIONAL — CPU works but is slow)
   - NVIDIA GPU + CUDA toolkit required
   - Set detection.device and pose.device to 'cuda:0'


